cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Satsuma, please cite it as below."
title: "Satsuma: A Data Mapping Language"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Louw
    given-names: Thorben
    affiliation: Equal Experts
  - name: Equal Experts
    website: "https://www.equalexperts.com/"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/EqualExperts/satsuma-lang"
url: "https://github.com/EqualExperts/satsuma-lang"
abstract: >-
  Satsuma is a domain-specific language for source-to-target data mapping,
  designed to replace ad hoc spreadsheets and verbose structured specs
  with a format that is human-readable, machine-parseable, and suitable
  for AI-assisted data integration workflows.
keywords:
  - data mapping
  - source-to-target
  - domain-specific language
  - ETL
  - data integration
  - tree-sitter
